fasttravel.title: Hov
fasttravel.descr: Village known throughout all of Skellige for the infamous arena which once hosted fierce fights between the mightiest warriors in the isles

fasttravel.title: Svorlag
fasttravel.descr: The village was founded by the mythical Sove, who killed a terrifying and bloodthirsty chimera on this spot

fasttravel.title: Old Watchtower
fasttravel.descr: The ruins of an old watchtower in which, according to legend, a crazed Koviri princess once locked herself up, convinced only a man able to free her from this tower would be fit to be her husband. No one even tried, however, the princess died of old age and the tower fell into disrepair with the passage of time

fasttravel.title: Bay Of Winds
fasttravel.descr: Three generations ago this bay was a popular meeting spot for the local youth. Then one night a terrible storm broke out and the sea pounded into the beach, swallowing up several merry-makers and dragging them out to a watery grave

fasttravel.title: Yngvar's Fang
fasttravel.descr: This mountain peak was named after the mythical bear which, according to legend, was defeated by Tyr, the heroic founder of Clan Tuirsearch

fasttravel.title: Urialla Harbor
fasttravel.descr: On account of their mastery of their craft and painstaking attention to detail, the shipwrights working in this harbor are considered the best in the isles

fasttravel.title: Trail to Yngvar's Fang
fasttravel.descr: This is the start of the mountain trail leading to Yngvar's Fang, the pride and glory of An Skellig

fasttravel.title: The Pali Gap Coast
fasttravel.descr: Elders say an isolated cave on this coast was once used as a retreat by the world's most famous bard (before the rise of Dandelion, that is): the great Xirdneh of Zanguebar, renowned from Nazair to the Dragon Mountains for his ferocious lute-strumming

fasttravel.title: Kaer Almhult
fasttravel.descr: Built centuries ago to serve as the home keep for the kings of Skellige. In practice, however, each ruler preferred to keep to his clan's seat, and Kaer Almhult was left unused. Eventually the decision was made to turn it into a prison, and today the fortress is a crumbling ruin

fasttravel.title: Tor Gvalch'ca
fasttravel.descr: An ancient tower which was erected in the days when elves were the unchallenged masters of these lands

fasttravel.title: Abandoned Village
fasttravel.descr: This village's residents were forced to abandon it in a hurry when the Ice Giant unexpectedly awoke and decided to make known his wrath

fasttravel.title: Urskar
fasttravel.descr: The villagers here were famous for their love of pickled herring. They ate it for breakfast, dinner, and supper, and even made jams and compotes out of it

fasttravel.title: Clan Tordarroch Forge
fasttravel.descr: A famous forge where the best tools and weapons in all of Skellige were once made. When the Ice Giant took over the isle, he turned it into his larder

fasttravel.title: Dorve Ruins
fasttravel.descr: Ruins of a village destroyed by the Ice Giant

fasttravel.title: Marlin Coast
fasttravel.descr: Until quite recently this beach was frequented by fishermen come to fish marlins out of the nearby waters

fasttravel.title: Gull Point
fasttravel.descr: Sea fowl come from miles around to congregate on this scrap of barren land, mate and lay eggs

fasttravel.title: Eldberg Lighthouse
fasttravel.descr: Lighthouse built on orders of Jarl Skjordal in order to light the sea and route to Arinbjorn

fasttravel.title: Arinbjorn
fasttravel.descr: A village whose calm is only occasionally disturbed by someone slapping another senseless or one comrade breaking a bottle of mead over his mate's head

fasttravel.title: Wild Shore
fasttravel.descr: A wild and untamed™ part of the isle's coastline. A favourite spot for bandits and lovers

fasttravel.title: Holmstein's Port
fasttravel.descr: Piers and docks for the village of Holmstein - Clan Drummond's chief port

fasttravel.title: Kaer Muire
fasttravel.descr: This fortress has served as Clan Drummond's home base for centuries. the days when it was new and in full repair are a distant memory now

fasttravel.title: Fornhala
fasttravel.descr: Mysterious abandoned village

fasttravel.title: Sund
fasttravel.descr: Small village whose inhabitant are for the most part shepherds

fasttravel.title: Elverum Lighthouse
fasttravel.descr: The former keeper of this lighthouse was a confirmed eccentric. In addition to caring for the lighthouse, he also wrote poetry and wove carpets, was known to strip naked and run laps around the lighthouse at noon while shouting "sound mind in a sound body" and for breakfast would eat nothing but fish tails

fasttravel.title: Fayrlund
fasttravel.descr: This small village has gained great renown as home to the best hunters in Skellige

fasttravel.title: Fyresdal
fasttravel.descr: Those living here are tough on the outside, but soft and tender within

fasttravel.title: Ruined Inn
fasttravel.descr: Ruined and burned-down tavern which once treated locals and travelers to the best roast lamb around

fasttravel.title: Palisade
fasttravel.descr: The remnants of the palisade that once marked the border between the territories of Clan Drummond and Clan an Craite

fasttravel.title: Boxholm
fasttravel.descr: Boxholm was once a thriving village serving the nearby fortress, Kaer Nyssen. Today nothing remains of this past glory but a pile of stones, some debris, and fading memories

fasttravel.title: Rannvaig
fasttravel.descr: Fifteen years ago, one of the fishermen of Rannvaig bagged an enormous halibut, and from that moment on all the other villagers have devoted their lives to beating his record

fasttravel.title: Distillery
fasttravel.descr: A shroud of secrecy envelops this place. All that is known is that it produces the finest hooch in all of skellige

fasttravel.title: Grotto
fasttravel.descr: An isolated-off locale that can only be reached by boat

fasttravel.title: Blandare
fasttravel.descr: Unusually for a Skellige village, Blandare is located inland, far from any shore. Its inhabitants scratch out a living through mining and shepherding

fasttravel.title: Druids' Camp
fasttravel.descr: Camp pitched by druids investigating the magic cataclysm which devastated the nearby woods

fasttravel.title: Redgill
fasttravel.descr: This village's inhabitants fled in a panic when a mysterious magic cataclysm struck the surrounding area

fasttravel.title: Whale Graveyard
fasttravel.descr: The isle's inhabitants come here and gather bones which they use to build their huts

fasttravel.title: Gedyneith
fasttravel.descr: An oak which is sacred to all Skelligers, as it is worshiped both by druids and Freya's disciples. The Isle's most important ceremonies are held here, including weddings and royal coronations

fasttravel.title: Gedyneith
fasttravel.descr: An oak which is sacred to all Skelligers, as it is worshiped both by druids and Freya's disciples. The Isle's most important ceremonies are held here, including weddings and royal coronations

fasttravel.title: Abandoned Sawmill
fasttravel.descr: Though located depp in the forest, an ideal place for lumber harvesting, the sawmill now lies abandoned and unused

fasttravel.title: Kaer Gelen
fasttravel.descr: This old fort's ruins attract the sort whom one would not want to run into in a dark alley

fasttravel.title: Miners' Camp
fasttravel.descr: Small camp which local miners use as a base during their gold prospecting expeditions into the mountains to the north

fasttravel.title: Rogne
fasttravel.descr: This mountain settlement is home to tough folk of indomitable spirit

fasttravel.title: Crossroads
fasttravel.descr: Fork in the road leading to Kaer Trolde

fasttravel.title: Kaer Trolde Harbor
fasttravel.descr: One of the busiest ports in Skellige. Goods from every corner of the world are brought here to be sold and traded

fasttravel.title: Bridge to Kaer Trolde
fasttravel.descr: This stone bridge was, according to legend, carved single-handedly by Grymmdjarr, the heroic founder of Clan an Craite

fasttravel.title: Ancient Crypt
fasttravel.descr: Though Skelligers are famed for bravery bordering on madness, there are certain places which even they keep their distance from. This is one of them

fasttravel.title: Yustianna's Grotto
fasttravel.descr: Yustianna was a pirate born of a Skelliger from Clan an Craite and a captive woman taken during a raid. In her time she was feared on the Continent from Ofir to Zanguebar. Known for her skill as a navigator and unmatched master of various weapons, she quickly became the terror of the Great Sea, and when she returned to Skellige, they say this cave is where she hid her loot

fasttravel.title: Giants' Toes
fasttravel.descr: In truth simply a normal rock formation shaped by centuries of wind and water, islanders believe Uroboros punished giants who opposed his will by turning them into these stones

fasttravel.title: Harviken
fasttravel.descr: Home seat to Clan Dimun, and the location where Holger Blackhand divvies out the loot after every successful raid

fasttravel.title: Trottheim
fasttravel.descr: This village was once famed across all of Skellige for the fact that it was inhabited exclusively by women, all their men having died during one raid or another

fasttravel.title: Larvik
fasttravel.descr: The largest village on Hindarsfjall and home seat to Donar, head of Clan an Hindar. Its inhabitants are just and god-fearing folk, traditionalists strident in their devotion to Freya

fasttravel.title: Lurthen
fasttravel.descr: Lurthen's most famous inhabitant was a certain Peter Pijus, known for the fact that he was able to drink an entire barrel of mead in one go and remain standing

fasttravel.title: Isolated Hut
fasttravel.descr: They say this was once home to a herbalist who came to the isles from the continent. Unable to find a place in any of the nearby villages, she settled in this seaside hut, where she recieved the occasional visitor in need of magic creams of bandages

fasttravel.title: Lofoten Cemetery
fasttravel.descr: The inhabitants of Lofoten often visit this small cemetery to care for the graves of their loved ones and ask Freya for blessings in the afterlife

fasttravel.title: Lofoten
fasttravel.descr: Once a rich and vibrant village, today Lofoten is a ravaged and crumbling ruin

fasttravel.title: Freya's Garden
fasttravel.descr: Garden dedicated to the goddess Freya. Once beautiful and filled with thousands of fragrant blooms and herbs, today it lies abandoned and untended
